text: Manuel José Blanco y Calvo de Encalada (April 21, 1790 – September 5, 1876) was a vice-admiral in the Chilean Navy. He later became a political figure, and the first President of the provisional government of Chile in 1826. == References == Category:1790s births Category:1876 deaths Category:Chilean military people Category:Chilean politicians Category:Presidents of Chile
title: Manuel Blanco Encalada
